! Model Context Protocol (MCP) Technical Notes

!! Overview
MCP is a protocol that enables seamless integration between AI models and external tools/services.

!! Key Components

!!! Server
* Implements tool definitions
* Handles tool execution requests
* Manages state and resources

!!! Transport
* STDIO-based communication
* JSON-RPC protocol
* Bidirectional message flow

!!! Tools
* Defined with schemas (using Zod)
* Input validation
* Structured output format

!! Implementation Notes

```javascript
// Basic tool structure
const toolDefinition = {
  name: 'tool_name',
  description: 'What this tool does',
  inputSchema: zodSchema,
};
```

!! Best Practices
# Keep tool operations atomic
# Validate all inputs
# Provide clear error messages
# Use descriptive tool names

